npm i nodemon -D ===> -D What is this 
this is DevDependencies
What is DevDependencies..?
it is needed in Development environment
not needed in production world because we d not neet to restart the server again n again
when we develop project we need express, ejs , nodemon thats why we install them but for deployment DevDependencies will not install which makes project size smaller shorter

crypto hash
A cryptographic hash is a one-way mathematical function that takes any input (password, file, data) and converts it into a fixed-length string called a hash.
2️⃣ Data Integrity

Used to verify data hasn’t been changed.
3️⃣ Authentication & Security

Used in:

JWT signing

API tokens

Digital signatures

4️⃣ Blockchain & Crypto

Each block stores previous block’s hash

Any change breaks the chain → tamper-proof